title: High School sports
text:
Published: Sat, October 3, 2015 @ 12:00 a.m. 
High School sports 
Maplewood 10, Grand Valley 0 
MECCA 
Thomas Rink set a Maplewood record with seven goals as the Rockets defeated the Mustangs in Northeastern Athletic Conference play on Thursday. Paul Kellar, Thomas Dorsey III and Evan Hunter also scored goals for Maplewood (9-3-1). Kellar, Rink, Austin Miner and Matthew Sheely had assists. Miner made two saves. 
Salem 2, Niles 0 
NILES 
Andrew Pasco and Garrett Dickey scored goals Thursday as the Quakers (6-5-1) moved over .500 for the first time in three seasons. Andre Tonkinson had an assist. Salem (6-5-1) will host state-ranked South Range (No. 7 in Division III) on Monday night. JV: Salem, 4-1.
